This is the final execution plan for your Adaptive Signature Verification System scaled for 50,000 users.
1. The Enrollment Phase (The Foundation)
Method: Multi-Sample Baseline Collection.
Action: Collect 20 signatures per user (7 Relaxed, 7 Rushed, 6 Standing).
Algorithm: Centroid Calculation (Mean Vector).
Output: Create a Master Vector (Average of all 20) and a Gallery JSON (All 20 individual vectors).
2. The AI Architecture (The Brain)
Model Type: Siamese Neural Network.
Backbone: ResNet-50 or MobileNetV2 (for speed).
Loss Function: Triplet Loss (to maximize the gap between genuine and forgery).
Deployment Format: ONNX Runtime (Converts .pth to a high-speed production engine).
3. Image Pre-Processing (The Cleaning)
Client-Side: Canvas-to-Tensor Conversion (Done in the browser/app).
Algorithm 1: Zhang-Suen Thinning (Skeletonization) — Reduces strokes to 1-pixel width.
Algorithm 2: Min-Max Normalization — Resizes and centers the signature to 224x224 pixels.
4. Database & Storage Strategy (The Library)
Database: MySQL with client_srno as the Primary Key.
Storage Way: Hybrid Schema:
master_vector: Stored as a Binary BLOB (Fast 1-to-1 matching).
gallery_vectors: Stored as a JSON Array (Variation lookup).
Caching: Redis pre-loading of the current shift’s Master Vectors.
5. Verification Workflow (The Logic)
Tier 1: Master Match — Compare Live Vector vs. Master Vector using Cosine Similarity.
If Score > 0.95: Access Granted (Instant).
Tier 2: Gallery Search — If Tier 1 fails, compare Live Vector against all 20 Gallery Vectors.
If any score > 0.85: Access Granted.
Tier 3: Active Learning Update — If Tier 1 was successful, perform a FIFO (First-In-First-Out) update. Replace the oldest gallery vector with the new one.
6. Scaling for 50k Users (The Performance)
Method: Asynchronous Processing.
Strategy: Use a Task Queue (like Celery or RabbitMQ) to handle the "Active Learning" database updates in the background so the user doesn't have to wait at the screen.
Edge Computing: Perform all image "cleaning" (Pre-processing) on the user's device to save server CPU.
Summary of Algorithm Names to Use:
Siamese Network (Feature Extraction)
Cosine Similarity (Distance Metric)
Zhang-Suen (Thinning/Skeletonization)
Centroid/Mean Shift (Master Vector creation)
FIFO Buffer (Gallery management)
